    "9f9a1dc1-de29-4705-bba6-98eb2b6b1e71": {
      "type": "rich-text",
      "blocks": {
        "f32a8001-5016-4ef3-9ecc-abd64a1c751c": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "TIP #6 BRING YOUR OWN FOOD",
            "heading_size": "h1"
          }
        },
        "6adfc57c-fb37-4b69-b231-cce0feaf808e": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>While everyone loves a burger, or an obligatory noodle-based food bowl, festival food can wind up being super expensive, especially if you’re there for a few days.<\/p><p>So, take as much food with you as you can. Fruit, crackers, cereal bars - they’re all easy to take with you and will give you fuel for the day ahead.<\/p><p>If you’re camping, you might want to consider bringing a small stove. It will be sure to save you money on larger meals, and it’s actually fun sitting around the stove cooking up some food together. Just make sure to check the campsite rules before you go.<\/p>",
            "description_padding": 32
          }
        },
        "a7d9441b-d707-4159-8c9f-bf9dcc32442c": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "TIP #7 PRINT A MAP AND ARTIST SCHEDULE",
            "heading_size": "h2"
          }
        },
        "25ffc2d0-2d41-44a5-8723-cb85ab221002": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Printing a map and artist schedule is a smart plan. The one thing you don’t want to do is miss your favorite artist on stage.<\/p><p>Check out the map before you go, it’s a great way to get your bearings. You can identify where the important facilities are, like toilets, first-aid, lost property, information points and much more. <\/p><p>If you can’t print them off in advance, pick one up when you arrive. Just make sure that you leave some time to have a little look around before the fun starts.<\/p>",
            "description_padding": 32
          }
        }
      },
