    "d1537d8c-2857-4fa6-ae59-fb97fb3b21a0": {
      "type": "rich-text",
      "blocks": {
        "3e7e9421-23aa-4498-ae75-eabce93a850f": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "TIP #8 BRING YOUR OWN TOILET PAPER",
            "heading_size": "h0"
          }
        },
        "41af495c-33da-4723-85b5-afd3ac147c12": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>The toilets at festivals have a bad rep, and unfortunately, it’s for good reason. <\/p><p>Of course, they’re meant to be stocked with toilet paper, but that’s not to say they will be. And even if they are, it might have been dropped on the floor, or - even worse - down the toilet. <\/p><p>So, come prepared. Bring your own roll (or three) and stay one step ahead. You’ll be glad you did.<\/p>",
            "description_padding": 32
          }
        },
        "aac5f6ce-da74-44cb-a119-0af09a5da234": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "TIP #9 STAY ENERGIZED",
            "heading_size": "h1"
          }
        },
        "66d24fb7-e7a2-40b3-afe7-68b195aa0319": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Festivals are non-stop, so you’re going to need to keep yourself energized. Remember that food and water are your friends, and the key to keeping you going. <\/p><p>Eat foods that will also help keep you hydrated, such as bananas, kale and watermelon. Fruit will help cool your body down. And nuts are an ideal choice as they’re packed full of protein, and you can buy them in bulk to bring with you. They’re healthy, portable and super tasty, too.<\/p>",
            "description_padding": 32
          }
        },
        "a2cbe5eb-3fd2-4541-a376-b8783d723eb6": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "TIP #10 PACK A PORTABLE CHARGER",
            "heading_size": "h1"
          }
        },
        "68c41477-9dda-4eca-94d9-6d05dd42986e": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Odds are, your phone battery is going to die on you. At least three times. <\/p><p>And let’s face it, you’re going to want it charded and alive, ready to take that perfect selfie, or film that live set you’ve been dying to see.<\/p><p>So take a <a href=\"https:\/\/thefestivals.uk\/best-festival-portable-charger\/\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">portable charger<\/span><\/a> with you, or a power bank. They’ll often last the entire festival. <\/p><p>It’s also becoming more common for festivals to offer charging facilities for phones and iPads. And sometimes these facilities are even solar powered. So keep a lookout!<\/p>",
            "description_padding": 32
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "3e7e9421-23aa-4498-ae75-eabce93a850f",
