    "6d4c2fb5-44b7-4c64-81f0-922af5635782": {
      "type": "image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "1386a1a4-aef0-4a18-8ef8-ea0462fb9c7a": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "TIP #11 PACK LIGHT",
            "heading_size": "h2"
          }
        },
        "template--15758497120452__6d4c2fb5-44b7-4c64-81f0-922af5635782-16668720159e416163-1": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>It may be tempting to pack tons of great, festival-ready outfits, especially if you’re a first-timer. But try to resist this urge. The last thing you’ll want to do is lug around a heavy bag, especially when you have camping gear to transport, too. <\/p><p>So pack minimally. Yes, air mattresses are comfy, but sleeping pads are just as nice and a lot easier to deal with. Backpacking tents are much lighter than regular tents too - something to keep in mind.<\/p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
      },
