    "3c067c96-000a-4dfc-9716-2870ba743bb2": {
      "type": "rich-text",
      "blocks": {
        "template--15787235770564__3c067c96-000a-4dfc-9716-2870ba743bb2-166997577179d60747-0": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "TIP #12 BUY A WRIST STRAP FOR YOUR PHONE OR CAMERA",
            "heading_size": "h1"
          }
        },
        "template--15787235770564__3c067c96-000a-4dfc-9716-2870ba743bb2-166997577179d60747-1": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>To get the best view, most people want to hold their phone or camera above their heads. This works well, until someone bumps into you and it spirals to the floor, becoming one with the mud. <\/p><p>Investing in a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.amazon.co.uk\/dp\/B08M9ZJMM6?crid=2S2737TFHAUGI&keywords=camera%2Bstrap%2Bfor%2Bphone&sprefix=camera%2Bstrap%2Bfor%2Bphon%2Caps%2C141&ref_=as_li_ss_tl&language=en_US&sr=8-4&linkCode=gs2&linkId=04f856d0a3befb6915824ba28b133f48&tag=travelandd-21&th=1\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">wrist strap<\/span><\/a> means that even if you lose your grip, you’ll keep your camera attached to you. You can even buy a phone case with a wrist strap attached, for double phone protection. <\/p>",
            "description_padding": 32
          }
        },
        "848867f0-2e06-403b-afa4-0f5b18a09786": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "TIP #13 REMEMBER YOUR CAMPING ESSENTIALS",
            "heading_size": "h1"
          }
        },
        "77525898-15ec-412a-ac4f-1777929099ee": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>You don’t need a lot, but there are some <a href=\"https:\/\/luminaid.com\/blogs\/news\/camping-must-haves-and-essentials\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">vital essentials<\/span><\/a> that you’ll be happy you brought along for the ride. A first-aid kit is a must. As is a solar-powered lantern. It can be dark outside your tent if you’re a way away from the center of everything.<\/p><p>Make sure you choose a smart camping spot, too. You might want to be in the middle of the action, but for the light sleepers out there it’s wise to find a spot that’s not too close to the stage or other tents. Find the balance somewhere in between - not too close, but not so far that it’s a huge hike back to the festival the next morning. <\/p><p>Be sure to check out all the festival camping tips published by the festival before you go.<\/p>",
            "description_padding": 32
          }
        },
        "eb502eed-ab97-4e18-b5bc-735de6b93580": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "TIP #14 YOUR SHOE CHOICE MATTERS",
            "heading_size": "h1"
          }
        },
        "1eeb8adb-4709-41d9-a70e-517d0b105347": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>There’s no doubt: festivals are full of fashion inspiration. So while a lot of thought may go into aesthetics when it comes to your shoe choice, be sure to remember the practicalities too. People will step on your toes a lot. You’ll be standing even more. And by the end it’ll seem like you’ve been walking for days (because you will have been). Keeping your feet happy means that you’ll enjoy your festival experience for longer. <\/p>",
            "description_padding": 32
          }
        }
      },
