    "af390d07-1718-439f-8200-0f2218d8afe9": {
      "type": "rich-text",
      "blocks": {
        "eb538dc9-1226-4d26-80c3-0e39cc36cf37": {
          "type": "text",
          "disabled": true,
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>Relaxation techniques<\/strong><\/p><p>As phonophobia is often linked with issues such as anxiety and stress, sometimes the effects can be reduced by some simple relaxation techniques. <\/p><p>Meditation and yoga can go a long way toward giving you a sense of peace, calmness, and balance that can help subdue phonophobia, as well as improve your overall mental and physical health. <\/p><p>The practice of meditation can help you to find your center and bring about some level of inner peace – making it a key tool when battling phobias.<\/p><p><strong>Therapy<\/strong><\/p><p>Like with any phobia, getting help from a professional is the best way toget a handle on your phonophobia.<\/p><p>Fortunately, there are a number of different types of therapy that have shown positive results when being used to treat phobias. Let’s take a look at the two most common:<\/p><p><\/p>",
            "description_padding": 32
          }
        },
        "061cfd15-5c18-4953-9cca-a9e627631923": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "TIP #15 KEEP HYDRATED",
            "heading_size": "h1"
          }
        },
        "b4ecbf04-e53d-4563-a498-09502e87b0ff": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>You’re having fun in the sun, dancing and enjoying a few beers – it’s easy to forget to drink water. <\/p><p>But as you’re going to be doing a lot of walking in the summer heat, the last thing you want is to become <a href=\"https:\/\/www.mayoclinic.org\/diseases-conditions\/dehydration\/symptoms-causes\/syc-20354086\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">dehydrated<\/span><\/a>, which is sure to spoil the fun. <\/p><p>The thing is, when your body is dehydrated, it can lead to low blood pressure, reduced cognitive performance and, in some extreme cases, medical emergencies. So it’s important you keep up your fluid intake. <\/p><p>And remember, it’s likely that you’ll be facing long queues to buy expensive bottled water. So think about taking your own refillable <a href=\"https:\/\/surviveyourfestival.com\/choosing-the-best-festival-water-bottle\/\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">water bottle<\/span><\/a> – it’s cheaper, eco-friendly, and you’ll avoid the queues. <\/p>",
            "description_padding": 32
          }
        }
      },
